data.title: Cool, friedly, little place
data.text: The Cuban sandwich is outta sight! The roast pork is tasty and tender. The staff is friendly and helpful. Get a cup of Cuban coffee. It's really good!

data.title: Home Cooking Cuban/Puerto Rican Style
data.text:
Eaten at this restaurant twice, and the food was delicious and freshly made.  I had the Ropa Vieja with Cuban rice and plantains.  The second visit I had the Paella.  I should have stuck with the first choice, as the Paella was not your typical Spanish style, the ingredients/seafood was not what I expected and at $14 for lunch I found it pricey.
If you are Cuban or Puerto Rican, you will love this place, but let me warn you that the Cuban Sandwiches are not as authentic as I'm used to.
They also moved from their Shiloh location to San Bernardo, which is quite a bit further to get to.
Wish them the best, but time will tell if the clientele will be loyal and pay the prices for lunch which runs an easy $20.00/tip.

data.title: Fantastic Meal
data.text: Came along with a group of friends had never eaten Cuban food before. Every thing looked delicious and we enjoyed ourselves. Tostones were remarkable, could eat then all day! Portions were huge and a great price too.

data.title: Very tasty
data.text: Address is actually 416 Shiloh.  Food - very tasty, service friendly.  Empanadas con carne y queso - VERY nice.  Ropa vieja - VERY nice - ask for it poco picante.  Plantains - very nice.  Tostones rellenos - very nice.  We will definitely go back.
